RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 86. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE AUGUST 12, 2022. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 12 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SLITHER staled the front runner while racing in the three path, was encouraged through the turn to draw closer to the lead horse, was still chasing in the upper stretch, was driven and hand ridden, continued to close, finally passed the tiring front runner at the eighth pole and drew away for the win. LAUGHINGSAINTSSONG vied for the lead, set the pace while racing along the rail, led all the way to the eighth pole, began to tire and relinquished the lead to a closing rival but had done enough early to hold on for second place money. CARLOS PUNCH raced from mid pack in the three path and maintained that position through out. MORRICONE broke out just a bit, trailed the field through out while racing in the three path.

ENTRY.NAME: Slither
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, 3w, encouraged stretch, led 1/8, drew away

ENTRY.NAME: Morricone
ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed through out while racing in the three path.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 2 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 89. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 12 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FATHER RED raced in the four path as he staked the leaders from the outside of the second tier of horses, moved up at the half mile pole, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, was still closing in on the leader in the upper stretch, was kept on point and drew beside to challenge for the lead at the eighth pole, took over from the and was hand ridden to the wire for the win. HAPPY BOY ROCKET stalked the early speed from the three path, launched a bid at the three eights pole, raced between horses, challenged for the lead at the five sixteenth pole, was in the lead at the quarter pole, was challenged by a closing rival and gave up the lead but continued to run and was bale to hold on to second place. CHIEF CHEETAH raced from mid pack on the rail, started to edge out on the backside into the three and four path, launched a bit at the three eighths pole, split rivals, shifted out into the seven path nearing the quarter pole, closed down the stretch under encouragement and made up ground coming away with third today. AMERICAN SMOOTH vied for the lead, led in a set with another determined front runner, set the pace while racing on the rail, then flattened out near the quarter pole. STOCKPILER was off a bit slow, was allowed to settle in hands along the rail, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, improved position through the turn, was still off the pace in the upper stretch, shifted out into the six path at the eighth pole, found his best stride and gained ground with each stride. WESLEYAN was sharp in the first few jumps, asked to rate through the first turn, was in a stalking position down the back side, launched a bid at the three eights pole, saved ground through out but had no rally in the stretch. BOULDERING was off the pace early shifted into the five path, started to improve position at the half mile pole, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, raced between foes and moved into the upper stretch but had no kick. MAJOR DEAL was off of the pace and in the six path, improved position on the back side, was six wide in the turn, but to no avail. INFINITE MORO vied for the lead from the far outside, shifted into the two path while matching another rival for the lead, co led and participated in pace setting early then tired at the five sixteenth pole and retreated.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WITHOUT A SONG was off in the middle of the field, was hustled a bit, was cued at the five eighths pole, was in full stride and racing five wide by the half mile pole, circled the field in the four path, continued to race in the four path down the stretch, took the lead at the eighth pole and pulled away in the last sixteenth for the win. SEA FORCE vied for the lead and raced first four wide, then two wide, set the pace, led until the eighth pole then was collared, but still kept on and was second best today. SAN JUAN HILL stalked the early leaders from the four path, raced in between horses, was patient and waited until after the three eighths pole to launched a bid, raced in the two path through the turn and into the upper stretch, hit his best stride late and closed well. KILO KEY was off a step slow, trailed the field early, raced in the three path, launched a bid at the half mile pole, gained ground and improved position through the bend, closed in the stretch but to no avail. CADILLAC COWBOY vied for the lead, then settled off of the leader and stalked from the four path, stayed in that position until near the quarter pole where he faded. SOCIAL APPEAL was off the pace, raced between foes and mildly improved late. DOCE DE LA NOCHE raced from the middle of the filed on the rail, but never got involved. PROSPECTOR'S POINT was off the pace, raced on the rail, showed little. LEVY BILL made no impact.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 18000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 12, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PINCH ME A PENNY stalked the pace from the five path, launched a bid at the three eights pole, hooked the front runners at the five sixteenth pole, shook one, battled with the other early leader until the three sixteenth pole, shook that foe and drew off down the stretch for the impressive win. SALUTE NOW was off a step slow, trailed the field while finding his stride, bid at the half mile pole, circled the field in the turn racing in the five path, closed with conviction, drifted in a bit down the lane but continued to gain ground and close with each stride, could not get to the winner but was better than the rest getting up for a game second. JIMMIE'S HALO was off a bit slow, improved position down the back side, raced in the four path, launched a bid at the three eighths and gained ground as he raced in between foes through the turn, was asked to close in the stretch but struggled to switch leads, started to loose ground, then finally switched but it was too late. JOEY'S GAME was off in mid pack, raced on the rail, traveled at his own pace as he saved ground, shuffled back a bit entering the turn, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, shifted out into the five path as he circled the field through the turn, then was asked to close but struggled to switch his lead and finished flat. BIG ACE stalked the pace from the three path, drew beside the early leader and set the next set of fractions as a set, was joined by a fast closing outside challenger at the five sixteenth pole, matched strides and battled into the stretch then BIG ACE gave way in the stretch. CHROMPTON vied for the lead, led while racing in the two path, was joined by another rival and set the next fractions as a set, then tired at the five sixteenth pole. PINK HIGGINS was off in the middle of the field, raced in between foes in the three path, maintained position through out, running an even race. BIG SCULLY was off mid pack, raced wide through out. DOUBLE PRIORITY showed little.
